reviews.review_text: Nice matrix Very nice matrix of this historic show. On an initial listen, I prefer it to the other matrix on the archive. The first set doesn't do much for me, but the 2nd set with Ornette is absolutely worth listening to. A welcome foray into experimentalism with a master of the art. Probably one of the best "Space"s ever.

This Matrix pull A very significant latter day show.  

This matrix captures the deep bass the soundboard is kissing,  as well as the incredible feeling in the room.   Really a perfect matrix.

This show is a complete mind fuck.  The Broken Arrow debut is probably the best version, and the Johnny B. Goode might be the greatest since 1978.

Don’t be deceived by the setlist of the pre-drums.. the band is playing wide open and floating on a cloud.  

And then there’s the Ornette Coleman part of the show, which is nothing less than groundbreaking for the band.
